definitions.definition: A box, now usually a large strong box with a secure convex lid .
examples: The clothes are kept in a chest .

definitions.definition: The place in which public money is kept; a treasury .
examples: You can take the money from the chest .

definitions.definition: ( anatomy ) The portion of the human body from the base of the neck to the top of the abdomen; the homologous area in some other animals.
examples: She had a sudden pain in her chest .
An anteroposterior radiograph found opacities throughout her chest .

definitions.definition: The front ( anterior ) surface of this portion of the torso .
examples: He has a tattoo on his chest , and another on his upper back.
The wild gorilla was beating its chest .
He avoided being seen gazing at her chest , although he dearly longed to stare.

definitions.definition: A hit or blow made with one's chest.
examples: She scored with a chest into the goal.
